        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 2:02PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 202 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Penrose, or 29 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving east at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo West, Pueblo Reservoir, Royal Gorge, Canon City, Florence, and
Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
